Did you know?

Even in the first transistor radio introduced by Regency and Texas Instruments, it was recognized that a simple biasing technique would be unsuitable for mass production. The four transistors in this radio needed to maintain a relatively stable bias despite manufacturing variations and extreme temperatures in different global locations. Consequently, each stage included "emitter degeneration" to stabilize the bias point.
