\end{equation*}
$$

This result, combined with $I_{C}=\beta I_{B}$, forms a system of equations for $I_{C}$ and $I_{B}$. As in previous examples, iterations are useful here, but the exponential dependence in Eq. (5.41) causes large fluctuations in intermediate solutions. To address this, we rewrite Eq. (5.41) as

