We initiate the circuit analysis by noting that the base voltage consistently remains below the collector voltage: $V_{X}=V_{Y}-I_{B} R_{B}$. This crucial feature, a consequence of self-biasing, ensures that $Q_{1}$ operates in the active mode irrespective of device and circuit parameters. For instance, even if $R_{C}$ increases indefinitely, $Q_{1}$ stays in the active region, a significant advantage over the circuit shown in Fig. 5.21.
