Next, we determine the collector bias current by assuming $I_{B} \ll I_{C}$; i.e., $R_{C}$ conducts a current equal to $I_{C}$, resulting in

$$
\begin{equation*}
V_{Y}=V_{C C}-R_{C} I_{C} . \tag{5.75}
\end{equation*}
$$

Additionally,

$$
\begin{align*}
V_{Y} & =R_{B} I_{B}+V_{B E}  \tag{5.76}\\
& =\frac{R_{B} I_{C}}{\beta}+V_{B E} \tag{5.77}
